verbose_text: The aqueous methanol extract of T. diversifolia leaves was separated by a bioassay guided purification procedure, while the most active compound was isolated and characterized as tagitinin C. Tagitinin C inhibited the seedling growth of cress, Lolium multiflorum Lam., Phleum pratense L., and Echinochloa crus-galli (L.) P.Beauv. at concentrations greater than 0.1 mM.
evidence: inhibited the seedling growth of cress, Lolium multiflorum Lam., Phleum pratense L., and Echinochloa crus-galli
